<div id="review_3709877653" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3709877653" />
    <a title="Natasha" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/30637467-natasha"><img alt="Natasha" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1621292421p2/30637467.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3709877653?book_show_action=true">Jan 05, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Natasha" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Natasha" href="/user/show/30637467-natasha">Natasha</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9781580911863" href="/book/show/730745.Sister_Outsider">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/30637467-natasha?shelf=justice-n-education">justice-n-education</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3709877653" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10722975279769380267">Wow. Just incredible. I cannot believe this is the first time I’ve read anything by Audre Lorde! This collection is marvelous and moving - felt like good sized chunks to digest at a time, but many times I couldn’t help myself - her prose just drew me deeper and deeper and I couldn’t stop reading. Now I want to read as much of her poetry as I can get my hands on. These essays and speeches so eloquently illuminate the emotion and power of Lorde’s work. I particularly loved “Poetry is Not a Luxury”</span>
  <span id="freeText10722975279769380267" style="display:none">Wow. Just incredible. I cannot believe this is the first time I’ve read anything by Audre Lorde! This collection is marvelous and moving - felt like good sized chunks to digest at a time, but many times I couldn’t help myself - her prose just drew me deeper and deeper and I couldn’t stop reading. Now I want to read as much of her poetry as I can get my hands on. These essays and speeches so eloquently illuminate the emotion and power of Lorde’s work. I particularly loved “Poetry is Not a Luxury” and all her discussions of the importance of nonrational/nonlinear thinking and doing. Not to mention the obvious overarching themes of race, gender, sexuality, class, and more - somehow I feel as if I’ve been made to believe that the idea/theory of intersectionality is radically recent. Lorde emphatically proves otherwise (she &amp; other Black folks have been saying this for ages upon ages - why didn’t I realize that?), and I dearly wish these essays and speeches were required educational material. Maybe if I had read this in high school I could have started learning/been made to face these truths about racism (and other overlapping injustices) from earlier on. Can not recommend this book/collection enough. </span>
  <a data-text-id="10722975279769380267" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


